.TH "ubi_detach_mtd_dev" 9 "ubi_detach_mtd_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_detach_mtd_dev \- detach an MTD device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_detach_mtd_dev
.BI "(int ubi_num "  ","
.BI "int anyway "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi_num" 12
UBI device number to detach from
.IP "anyway" 12
detach MTD even if device reference count is not zero
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function destroys an UBI device number \fIubi_num\fP and detaches the
underlying MTD device. Returns zero in case of success and -EBUSY if the
UBI device is busy and cannot be destroyed, and -EINVAL if it does not
exist.

Note, the invocations of this function has to be serialized by the
\fIubi_devices_mutex\fP.
